1
00:00:32,303 --> 00:00:36,307
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

2
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:32,279
DAEUNGJEON HALL

3
00:01:32,363 --> 00:01:35,700
The Heart of the Prajna Paramita Sutra.

4
00:01:35,825 --> 00:01:37,660
Avalokiteshvara Bodhisattva.

5
00:01:37,743 --> 00:01:41,038
Deep in the practice of Perfect Wisdom

6
00:01:41,122 --> 00:01:43,958
clearly saw that
all five aggregates are empty.

7
00:01:55,678 --> 00:01:57,430
Three of our agents are dead.

8
00:01:58,597 --> 00:02:00,224
We're backed into a corner.

9
00:02:00,891 --> 00:02:03,686
NATIONAL SECURITY ADVISOR,
KWON SOON-BOK

10
00:02:03,936 --> 00:02:05,396
Let's call off the operation.

11
00:02:05,938 --> 00:02:09,525
TEAM LEADER, ANTI-COMMUNIST INVESTIGATION
TEAM, JO SEONG-WON

12
00:02:11,235 --> 00:02:12,236
We got intel

13
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:14,864
that an NIS agent worked
with a North Korean on drugs.

14
00:02:14,947 --> 00:02:17,241
We spent six long months
chasing that single piece of intel.

15
00:02:18,451 --> 00:02:19,452
This is what we have to show for it.

16
00:02:19,535 --> 00:02:22,246
Our job is to work in the shadows
and serve our country.

17
00:02:23,164 --> 00:02:26,041
Are you just going to stand by
while one mole eats away

18
00:02:26,625 --> 00:02:27,626
at the country's foundations?

19
00:02:31,422 --> 00:02:32,882
The mole in the
National Intelligence Service.

20
00:02:33,382 --> 00:02:35,634
We have to catch him
and get justice for our fallen men.

21
00:02:37,845 --> 00:02:39,180
Do you know who it is?

22
00:02:48,272 --> 00:02:50,733
Han Gyeong-wook, Deputy Director
of the Anti-Communist Investigation Team.

23
00:02:51,192 --> 00:02:52,234
You know him well, don't you?

24
00:02:53,819 --> 00:02:54,820
But...

25
00:02:55,613 --> 00:02:58,282
why would a legend at catching spies
be working with North Korea?

26
00:02:58,407 --> 00:02:59,617
Isn't this disinformation?

27
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,869
This intel cost our agents' lives.

28
00:03:02,703 --> 00:03:04,955
- It's solid.
- Do you have any concrete proof?

29
00:03:06,248 --> 00:03:07,458
Concrete proof?

30
00:03:08,584 --> 00:03:09,585
I have it.

31
00:03:13,214 --> 00:03:16,425
A few days ago, a special op from
North Korea's Counterintelligence Bureau

32
00:03:17,301 --> 00:03:18,886
Black Pearl, defected.

33
00:03:19,887 --> 00:03:22,097
She fled, stealing a slush fund
from a high-ranking North Korean official

34
00:03:22,598 --> 00:03:24,016
and a USB drive with data

35
00:03:24,266 --> 00:03:25,893
on their smuggling operations.

36
00:03:25,976 --> 00:03:27,102
On that drive...

37
00:03:27,186 --> 00:03:28,979
is information about the drug deal

38
00:03:29,230 --> 00:03:30,981
between Han Gyeong-wook
and the North Korean officer.

39
00:03:31,649 --> 00:03:33,275
If we get our hands on that USB

40
00:03:33,734 --> 00:03:36,195
there's no way Han Gyeong-wook
can get out of this.

41
00:03:37,363 --> 00:03:38,364
But...

42
00:03:38,697 --> 00:03:39,949
there's one problem.

43
00:03:41,283 --> 00:03:43,869
We tried contacting Black Pearl
through back channels

44
00:03:44,036 --> 00:03:45,412
but the negotiations fell apart.

45
00:03:45,496 --> 00:03:49,250
JAPANESE INTELLIGENCE BUREAU AGENT,
SHIBASAKI MICHIKO

46
00:03:51,001 --> 00:03:52,419
Black Pearl plans to sell

47
00:03:52,503 --> 00:03:54,797
the info to the Japanese for a high price

48
00:03:55,047 --> 00:03:56,340
and she's trying to get away with it.

49
00:03:59,802 --> 00:04:02,096
In two days,
Black Pearl's taking a ship to Japan.

50
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:05,182
She'll rendezvous with the agent
on the ferry.

51
00:04:05,474 --> 00:04:06,851
We must intercept it before then.

52
00:04:06,934 --> 00:04:08,352
And if we fail?

53
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,814
Is there another way?

54
00:04:12,982 --> 00:04:13,983
No.

55
00:04:18,612 --> 00:04:19,822
If we don't stop them this time

56
00:04:20,573 --> 00:04:23,284
they'll flood the country
with a massive amount of drugs.

57
00:04:24,034 --> 00:04:26,745
Then it'll only be a matter of time
before South Korea is a narco-state.

58
00:04:29,498 --> 00:04:30,583
This operation...

59
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:34,211
needs someone who gets the job done,
no matter what.

60
00:04:35,462 --> 00:04:36,463
But...

61
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:39,300
Right now, there's no one I can trust.

62
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:41,719
I know just the person.

63
00:04:42,678 --> 00:04:46,473
Sir, are you aware that within
the National Intelligence Service...

64
00:04:46,807 --> 00:04:48,309
there's a unit that doesn't exist
in unofficial records?

65
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,443
It has only one agent.

66
00:05:00,571 --> 00:05:01,739
Who are you?

67
00:05:01,822 --> 00:05:03,991
He's only deployed on missions
where everyone else has failed.

68
00:05:04,575 --> 00:05:06,160
The National Intelligence Service's
top black ops agent.

69
00:05:09,121 --> 00:05:10,205
Attack!

70
00:05:43,614 --> 00:05:44,865
Codename...

71
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:47,451
Shadow.

72
00:05:49,453 --> 00:05:50,955
Even if we deploy Shadow

73
00:05:51,330 --> 00:05:53,082
there's still a chance
the information could leak.

74
00:05:53,582 --> 00:05:54,959
Chief Han's NIS network

75
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:56,377
is incredibly strong.

76
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:59,129
CHEONBULJEON

77
00:05:59,838 --> 00:06:00,923
This operation...

78
00:06:01,966 --> 00:06:03,467
will be conducted in absolute secrecy.

79
00:06:04,718 --> 00:06:06,887
Team Leader Jo, just you, me, and Shadow.

80
00:06:07,137 --> 00:06:08,138
Only the three of us will know.

81
00:06:10,474 --> 00:06:11,767
If this goes south...

82
00:06:13,769 --> 00:06:15,646
you could be in serious trouble, sir.

83
00:06:17,773 --> 00:06:19,692
To take down the great Han Gyeong-wook...

84
00:06:20,859 --> 00:06:22,528
I'm willing to put my own neck
on the line.

85
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,959
I regret that things
have turned out this way.

86
00:06:37,251 --> 00:06:39,837
I never expected this
from that bitch Black Pearl.

87
00:06:40,004 --> 00:06:41,672
So, what's the solution?

88
00:06:42,339 --> 00:06:45,175
DEPUTY DIRECTOR, NIS
HAN GYEONG-WOOK

89
00:06:45,634 --> 00:06:48,053
I'll try to use some local thugs
to clean this up.

90
00:06:49,013 --> 00:06:52,016
MAJOR RI CHOL-JIN,
MINISTRY OF THE PEOPLE'S ARMED FORCES

91
00:06:52,599 --> 00:06:55,144
Shadow, the agent
assigned to this operation...

92
00:06:56,020 --> 00:06:57,980
is a monster raised by the NIS.

93
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:01,066
A truckload of your pathetic rabble
won't make a difference.

94
00:07:02,526 --> 00:07:03,902
Fight a monster with a monster.

95
00:07:04,778 --> 00:07:05,946
On our side

96
00:07:06,071 --> 00:07:09,575
what if we deploy our top agent
who's skilled in South Korean ops?

97
00:07:10,159 --> 00:07:11,285
Your top agent?

98
00:07:19,793 --> 00:07:20,794
Bulgae.

99
00:07:21,420 --> 00:07:23,756
He's a disguise and Taekkyeon expert

100
00:07:24,089 --> 00:07:25,799
so his movements are phantom-like.

101
00:07:26,258 --> 00:07:29,136
Those weak little South Korean punks
won't be a match for him.

102
00:07:51,408 --> 00:07:53,994
I've never seen anyone
who could handle Bulgae.

103
00:07:56,663 --> 00:07:57,915
Trust me and leave it to him.

104
00:08:04,338 --> 00:08:05,839
I need a contingency plan.

105
00:08:07,591 --> 00:08:09,426
We'll go with a two-pronged operation.

106
00:08:11,678 --> 00:08:12,721
How interesting.

107
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:45,796
BOSS OF THE HWASAN SECT
HWANG HWA-SAN

108
00:08:47,798 --> 00:08:49,842
Well, you didn't come here

109
00:08:49,925 --> 00:08:52,594
just to rehash the old days.

110
00:08:53,846 --> 00:08:55,389
So what is it that you want?

111
00:08:56,306 --> 00:08:58,308
You're still as sharp as ever
at reading the room.

112
00:08:58,559 --> 00:09:00,727
How about we work together again?

113
00:09:00,894 --> 00:09:01,937
Who is it?

114
00:09:02,146 --> 00:09:04,273
To make the great Chief Han...

115
00:09:04,773 --> 00:09:06,191
this nervous.

116
00:09:09,611 --> 00:09:10,863
Don't cross the line.

117
00:09:11,864 --> 00:09:14,032
Find me one of your guys
who can get the job done.

118
00:09:14,116 --> 00:09:16,160
Not some run-of-the-mill punk.

119
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:17,828
I need someone who's the real deal.

120
00:09:20,038 --> 00:09:22,916
The real deal...

121
00:09:26,295 --> 00:09:29,381
I've got just the guy for you.

122
00:09:39,558 --> 00:09:41,727
He took down nationwide gangsters
who were armed to the teeth

123
00:09:42,144 --> 00:09:43,812
with his bare fists.

124
00:09:45,022 --> 00:09:46,607
He's a true fighter.

125
00:09:49,193 --> 00:09:51,195
I don't know who he's up against

126
00:09:51,862 --> 00:09:53,989
but one punch from my guy...

127
00:09:56,074 --> 00:09:57,492
will be enough to settle things.

128
00:10:41,954 --> 00:10:45,249
The package has top-secret documents
from our Republic.

129
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:48,502
We can't let the South Korean bastards
get their hands on it, can we?

130
00:10:49,544 --> 00:10:50,754
In South Korea

131
00:10:51,213 --> 00:10:53,173
an agent called Shadow
has already been deployed.

132
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,134
Rumor has it that bastard

133
00:10:56,510 --> 00:10:59,429
is the best agent in South Korea,
so be extremely careful.

134
00:11:01,431 --> 00:11:04,142
You must get the package before he does.

135
00:11:09,648 --> 00:11:10,649
Beom-ryong.

136
00:11:10,899 --> 00:11:12,859
What is our Hwasan Sect?

137
00:11:13,485 --> 00:11:14,569
Didn't we build this

138
00:11:14,653 --> 00:11:17,906
from nothing in Gangnam
with our bare hands?

139
00:11:18,490 --> 00:11:20,951
We may be taking orders
from Han Gyeong-wook

140
00:11:21,702 --> 00:11:25,038
but he's the type of guy
to find our weakness someday

141
00:11:25,330 --> 00:11:26,415
and stab us in the back.

142
00:11:27,082 --> 00:11:28,292
We can't trust someone like him

143
00:11:28,542 --> 00:11:30,544
with the fate of our organization.

144
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:32,754
It doesn't matter.

145
00:11:32,879 --> 00:11:35,007
NIS guy or North Korean.

146
00:11:35,215 --> 00:11:36,258
No matter what

147
00:11:36,591 --> 00:11:38,719
you have to get the package

148
00:11:39,011 --> 00:11:40,012
first.

149
00:11:45,017 --> 00:11:46,018
Ho-myeong.

150
00:11:46,518 --> 00:11:47,519
Han Gyeong-wook

151
00:11:47,769 --> 00:11:51,106
has the NIS, prosecution,
and politicians in his pocket.

152
00:11:51,565 --> 00:11:53,317
If this continues,
the evil things he's done...

153
00:11:55,068 --> 00:11:56,528
could be buried forever.

154
00:11:57,362 --> 00:12:00,073
This is the last chance
we have to catch him.

155
00:12:02,492 --> 00:12:03,618
Also, for this mission

156
00:12:03,869 --> 00:12:05,704
there's talk that Bulgae
is being deployed.

157
00:12:06,121 --> 00:12:07,247
Be extra careful.

158
00:12:07,622 --> 00:12:10,334
And you just focus
on securing the package.

159
00:12:11,043 --> 00:12:12,044
Got it?

160
00:12:47,996 --> 00:12:49,039
This mission...

161
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:52,000
is your last one as Shadow.

162
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:52,352
HAN GYEONG-WOOK, DEPUTY DIRECTOR,
NATIONAL INTELLIGENCE SERVICE

163
00:13:59,985 --> 00:14:00,986
What's the status?

164
00:14:01,069 --> 00:14:02,070
Something's gone wrong.

165
00:14:02,446 --> 00:14:03,864
We failed to secure the package.

166
00:14:04,698 --> 00:14:05,907
Did Jeong Ho-myeong take it?

167
00:14:05,991 --> 00:14:08,118
No, sir. A North Korean agent took it.

168
00:14:08,452 --> 00:14:10,412
But he disappeared with the package.

169
00:14:10,954 --> 00:14:12,330
Erase every trace.

170
00:14:12,622 --> 00:14:13,748
As for the missing package...

171
00:14:14,249 --> 00:14:16,084
we retrieve it no matter what.

172
00:14:20,338 --> 00:14:21,506
Hey, Team Leader Jo.

173
00:14:21,631 --> 00:14:22,716
What's the status?

174
00:14:26,052 --> 00:14:27,053
Got it.

175
00:14:27,137 --> 00:14:28,180
First...

176
00:14:28,263 --> 00:14:29,264
get to safety.

177
00:14:29,890 --> 00:14:31,349
Let's meet at the safe house.

178
00:14:45,405 --> 00:14:46,865
The bag's GPS...

179
00:14:46,948 --> 00:14:49,743
The last signal from Bulgae
was on Yeongseon Island.

180
00:14:50,368 --> 00:14:51,620
Now the operation has gone south

181
00:14:51,703 --> 00:14:53,163
Han Gyeong-wook won't just stand by.

182
00:14:53,497 --> 00:14:55,123
I've already erased all your records.

183
00:14:55,332 --> 00:14:57,709
You go to Yeongseon Island
and find Bulgae, okay?

184
00:14:57,876 --> 00:14:58,877
Just find him.

185
00:15:00,587 --> 00:15:01,588
No, don't come.

186
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:04,883
Don't come and just lay low
until I contact you, all right?

187
00:15:05,050 --> 00:15:06,343
I'll be in touch.

188
00:15:09,012 --> 00:15:10,013
Seong-won.

189
00:15:13,391 --> 00:15:14,392
Seong-won.

190
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,271
Seong-won!

191
00:15:26,655 --> 00:15:31,826
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

192
00:15:32,494 --> 00:15:34,913
10 YEARS LATER

193
00:15:34,996 --> 00:15:38,708
YEONGSEON ISLAND

194
00:15:47,509 --> 00:15:48,510
Excuse me?

195
00:15:49,678 --> 00:15:52,430
- Can you repeat that?
- I said it's male menopause.

196
00:15:52,764 --> 00:15:54,599
You've heard of male menopause, right?

197
00:15:55,767 --> 00:15:56,768
Menopause...

198
00:15:57,435 --> 00:15:58,687
Can men get that too?

199
00:15:58,812 --> 00:16:00,397
It's common in middle-aged men

200
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,524
with decreased male hormone levels.

201
00:16:02,732 --> 00:16:03,858
Hold on...

202
00:16:05,110 --> 00:16:07,237
I think there's been a mistake.
Could you check...

203
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,531
Your testosterone level

204
00:16:10,031 --> 00:16:11,992
is currently below the threshold.

205
00:16:13,118 --> 00:16:15,203
For now,
I'm prescribing you male hormones.

206
00:16:15,287 --> 00:16:17,622
Take them regularly,
and we'll monitor your progress.

207
00:16:17,998 --> 00:16:20,500
- Hormones?
- If you don't treat this

208
00:16:20,834 --> 00:16:22,836
your symptoms will only get worse.

209
00:16:24,254 --> 00:16:25,505
Symptoms?

210
00:16:26,172 --> 00:16:27,215
Like what?

211
00:16:27,299 --> 00:16:29,092
Fatigue, lethargy

212
00:16:29,634 --> 00:16:30,969
and sexual dysfunction.

213
00:16:32,929 --> 00:16:34,180
You could even get shorter.

214
00:16:41,146 --> 00:16:42,564
You are now...

215
00:16:42,647 --> 00:16:45,191
ten years in the past.

216
00:16:46,234 --> 00:16:48,486
What do you see in front of you?

217
00:16:51,781 --> 00:16:53,199
People.

218
00:16:53,575 --> 00:16:54,826
What are you

219
00:16:54,909 --> 00:16:57,037
and those people doing, Je-sun?

220
00:16:58,663 --> 00:17:00,957
I'm fighting them. It's 17 to 1.

221
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:03,251
They're no match for me.

222
00:17:07,797 --> 00:17:09,257
Open your eyes.

223
00:17:16,306 --> 00:17:17,599
It was so vivid.

224
00:17:18,642 --> 00:17:20,352
Are my memories coming back?

225
00:17:22,187 --> 00:17:25,357
I told you to stop watching
so many action movies, didn't I?

226
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:28,276
You're always infiltrating some place
or defusing a bomb.

227
00:17:28,777 --> 00:17:29,986
The hypnosis keeps failing

228
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:32,197
because it's all you ever think about.

229
00:17:32,322 --> 00:17:33,531
But I haven't watched any.

230
00:17:33,615 --> 00:17:35,825
I don't think
this hypnotherapy is working.

231
00:17:47,379 --> 00:17:48,421
Have you gained weight?

232
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:50,674
You're looking good.

233
00:17:53,551 --> 00:17:54,886
Oh, well...

234
00:17:55,804 --> 00:17:58,473
By the way, how's your health, Boss?

235
00:17:58,556 --> 00:18:00,517
I heard you had a bad time with the flu.

236
00:18:00,767 --> 00:18:03,770
Yeah. I bought some thermals
with the money you put on my books.

237
00:18:04,729 --> 00:18:05,980
So I'm all better now.

238
00:18:07,357 --> 00:18:08,650
But the package...

239
00:18:09,484 --> 00:18:10,735
Still no update?

240
00:18:12,862 --> 00:18:14,948
I'm sorry. I've failed you.

241
00:18:15,323 --> 00:18:16,908
But we're searching everywhere.

242
00:18:17,158 --> 00:18:18,451
We should have good news soon.

243
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:19,661
Okay.

244
00:18:22,831 --> 00:18:24,499
The Lord said it himself.

245
00:18:25,583 --> 00:18:27,585
"Knock, and the door will be opened."

246
00:18:28,002 --> 00:18:29,546
So knock. Knock until it opens.

247
00:18:29,629 --> 00:18:31,339
Knock! And don't give up.

248
00:18:31,506 --> 00:18:32,507
Amen.

249
00:18:33,216 --> 00:18:35,802
JUMBO 24

250
00:18:42,434 --> 00:18:43,518
Seoraksan.

251
00:18:44,978 --> 00:18:46,896
Seoraksan is a mountain
in Gangwon Province.

252
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:48,314
This is Yeongseon Island.

253
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,900
Are you being smart with me?

254
00:18:51,735 --> 00:18:53,653
I said I want cigarettes. Seoraksan.

255
00:18:55,947 --> 00:18:56,990
That brand...

256
00:18:57,323 --> 00:18:58,992
You're the only one who buys them

257
00:18:59,075 --> 00:19:00,827
so we're not stocking them anymore.

258
00:19:00,910 --> 00:19:02,620
I told you so many times.
Why won't you stock them?

259
00:19:04,164 --> 00:19:05,165
You...

260
00:19:07,917 --> 00:19:09,419
Do you have any idea who I am?

261
00:19:09,711 --> 00:19:10,712
Who might you be?

262
00:19:10,837 --> 00:19:12,964
- Because I have no idea.
- Damn it...

263
00:19:13,047 --> 00:19:15,049
- I can't hit a civilian.
- Go ahead.

264
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,260
I'm ready to quit anyway.

265
00:19:18,678 --> 00:19:19,721
Look at this punk.

266
00:19:20,013 --> 00:19:21,598
- All right, today's your lucky day.
- What are you doing?

267
00:19:21,765 --> 00:19:22,766
You're in for it now.

268
00:19:23,224 --> 00:19:24,684
You think you're the only one
who can take something off?

269
00:19:25,351 --> 00:19:26,519
I can do it too.

270
00:19:27,020 --> 00:19:28,021
This is so stressful.

271
00:19:28,521 --> 00:19:29,522
Sir!

272
00:19:36,446 --> 00:19:37,447
Manager Bong.

273
00:19:37,530 --> 00:19:38,531
Yes?

274
00:19:38,615 --> 00:19:41,951
- Manager Bong, the toilet's clogged.
- Oh, okay.

275
00:19:42,452 --> 00:19:43,620
Manager Bong.

276
00:19:43,995 --> 00:19:45,663
The printer's out of order again.

277
00:19:46,289 --> 00:19:47,373
Hurry.

278
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:54,881
Manager Bong.

279
00:19:56,424 --> 00:19:59,177
Come on, am I supposed to
handle the rebar shipment alone?

280
00:19:59,260 --> 00:20:00,512
No, it's just...

281
00:20:01,346 --> 00:20:02,847
The printer is broken.

282
00:20:18,863 --> 00:20:20,073
You fixed it.

283
00:20:20,782 --> 00:20:21,783
Thanks.

284
00:20:23,493 --> 00:20:24,494
Manager Bong.

285
00:20:25,078 --> 00:20:27,455
There's something
I've been meaning to tell you.

286
00:20:28,164 --> 00:20:29,874
You need to start saying no to tasks

287
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:31,251
that aren't part of your job.

288
00:20:31,376 --> 00:20:32,377
If you always say yes

289
00:20:32,460 --> 00:20:34,045
they'll see you as a pushover
and pile on more work.

290
00:20:34,128 --> 00:20:35,129
You're right.

291
00:20:35,296 --> 00:20:37,507
Okay. Next time, I'll refuse point-blank.

292
00:20:38,925 --> 00:20:39,926
Let's hurry.

293
00:20:40,385 --> 00:20:41,386
Manager Bong.

294
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:43,763
I'm sorry...

295
00:20:44,764 --> 00:20:46,307
but I'm a bit busy right now.

296
00:20:49,018 --> 00:20:50,395
Did I hear you correctly?

297
00:20:53,189 --> 00:20:54,190
You're busy?

298
00:20:59,612 --> 00:21:01,614
Even if you're busy,
I need you to wash my car.

299
00:21:02,031 --> 00:21:03,032
Make sure it's spotless.

300
00:21:13,668 --> 00:21:14,669
Nice pitch!

301
00:21:16,337 --> 00:21:17,338
Boss.

302
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:28,433
That's a dead ball.

303
00:21:28,558 --> 00:21:30,560
That was incredibly fast, though.

304
00:21:30,643 --> 00:21:32,437
Gosh, sorry.

305
00:21:32,812 --> 00:21:36,566
My arm is so powerful I have no control.

306
00:21:42,405 --> 00:21:43,406
Manager Bong.

307
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:46,326
There's no shine.

308
00:21:46,784 --> 00:21:48,161
Are you just going through the motions?

309
00:21:48,244 --> 00:21:49,329
I'm sorry.

310
00:21:50,330 --> 00:21:54,918
You really can't do anything right,
can you?

311
00:21:55,293 --> 00:21:58,963
What can I expect from a man
who doesn't even know who he is?

312
00:21:59,047 --> 00:22:01,799
God, what a half-wit.

313
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:06,930
Who else but me would hire
a flawed old man?

314
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:09,432
As if he knows anything. Unbelievable.

315
00:22:11,267 --> 00:22:12,268
Boss.

316
00:22:14,562 --> 00:22:15,563
What?

317
00:22:20,777 --> 00:22:22,362
Where should I polish?

318
00:22:23,404 --> 00:22:25,198
Are you joking me right now?

319
00:22:25,615 --> 00:22:27,992
You polish the hood, of course. The hood.

320
00:22:29,494 --> 00:22:31,704
Oh, for crying out loud.

321
00:22:35,124 --> 00:22:37,877
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

322
00:22:37,961 --> 00:22:39,587
Can we have some more pickled radish?

323
00:22:39,671 --> 00:22:43,633
- Where is ours?
- The pickled radish is coming.

324
00:22:43,716 --> 00:22:46,803
Yes, here is your order. Enjoy.

325
00:22:47,804 --> 00:22:50,515
- Mr. Kim, clear table one.
- Yes, okay.

326
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:51,641
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

327
00:22:51,724 --> 00:22:53,643
- We'd like to add a jajangmyeon.
- Yes, right away.

328
00:23:02,235 --> 00:23:03,236
Goodness.

329
00:23:03,528 --> 00:23:05,822
What took you so long?

330
00:23:06,072 --> 00:23:08,116
Wait, why is it only you
and my father-in-law?

331
00:23:08,616 --> 00:23:09,617
Where's Ji-woo's mom?

332
00:23:09,784 --> 00:23:11,869
She said she had a dance club meeting

333
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:13,037
and left suddenly.

334
00:23:13,162 --> 00:23:14,205
Again?

335
00:23:14,831 --> 00:23:16,958
Has she gone crazy for dancing?
What's with her lately?

336
00:23:17,041 --> 00:23:19,335
You live with her. How would I know?

337
00:23:19,419 --> 00:23:20,420
Mr. Jeong, we're backed up.

338
00:23:20,503 --> 00:23:21,879
- Get back inside. Quickly.
- Go.

339
00:23:21,963 --> 00:23:23,297
- Go in.
- And clear this table.

340
00:23:23,381 --> 00:23:24,382
Yes, yes.

341
00:23:59,709 --> 00:24:00,752
What are you looking at?

342
00:24:02,545 --> 00:24:04,047
SPICY STIR-FRIED PORK LUNCH BOX

343
00:24:07,258 --> 00:24:08,468
The expired food.

344
00:24:08,551 --> 00:24:10,053
I'm so sick of it.

345
00:24:13,598 --> 00:24:14,599
Hey.

346
00:24:14,682 --> 00:24:16,851
You're just hangry.

347
00:24:20,938 --> 00:24:23,232
Come on, it's not the first time
that old geezer's been a pain.

348
00:24:23,566 --> 00:24:24,984
Can't you just let it slide?

349
00:24:26,235 --> 00:24:27,320
This is a friendly convenience store.

350
00:24:27,904 --> 00:24:29,322
We have to keep our reputation, you know.

351
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:37,997
Boss, I can't live like this anymore.

352
00:24:38,498 --> 00:24:40,625
Let's find the item
and get off Yeongseon Island already.

353
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:43,169
I was wondering
when you'd bring that up again.

354
00:24:43,503 --> 00:24:45,338
Hey, if finding the item was so easy

355
00:24:45,463 --> 00:24:46,881
why do you think I'd still be here?

356
00:24:46,964 --> 00:24:49,717
Look, what was our mission for coming
to this island in the first place?

357
00:24:50,093 --> 00:24:52,762
Wasn't it to stop Jeong Ho-myeong,
the NIS agent who's after the item?

358
00:24:55,264 --> 00:24:56,265
Look.

359
00:24:56,682 --> 00:24:58,559
Jeong Ho-myeong's been more active

360
00:24:58,643 --> 00:25:00,061
and his movements are suspicious.

361
00:25:00,144 --> 00:25:01,771
I'm telling you, it feels like
he's about to make a move.

362
00:25:01,854 --> 00:25:04,065
Are you still tailing him
from Oran Chinese Restaurant?

363
00:25:04,941 --> 00:25:06,150
Yeah, now and then.

364
00:25:06,442 --> 00:25:08,402
It's my job.

365
00:25:08,945 --> 00:25:12,073
Hey, that woman is happily married
and living a good life.

366
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:14,033
Why on earth would he
go looking for the item?

367
00:25:14,325 --> 00:25:17,036
Instead of tailing him, you should be
thinking about boosting sales here.

368
00:25:17,870 --> 00:25:20,414
We're already spread thin just trying
to support the Boss in prison.

369
00:25:21,499 --> 00:25:23,626
- Does the Boss feel the same way?
- Yeah!

370
00:25:24,752 --> 00:25:26,045
That we should forget revenge

371
00:25:26,129 --> 00:25:28,172
and just focus on supporting him?

372
00:25:28,256 --> 00:25:29,257
Probably!

373
00:25:32,218 --> 00:25:33,928
Whatever you think, Boss

374
00:25:34,011 --> 00:25:36,180
I can't live as a convenience
store clerk anymore!

375
00:25:39,267 --> 00:25:40,810
Yeah? And what are you going
to do about it?

376
00:25:44,021 --> 00:25:45,022
Hey!

377
00:25:45,106 --> 00:25:48,484
JUMBO 24 FRIENDLY CONVENIENCE STORE
YEONGSEON ISLAND BRANCH WINS AWARD!

378
00:25:48,568 --> 00:25:51,404
WELCOME
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

379
00:25:51,487 --> 00:25:55,283
- Yes, one large sweet and sour pork.
- The road has become much safer...

380
00:25:57,076 --> 00:25:58,369
And now for the next news.

381
00:25:58,494 --> 00:26:00,621
With the Imcheon mayoral election
just around the corner

382
00:26:00,705 --> 00:26:03,958
Independent Kim Seon-jung
and Saehanjin Party's Han Gyeong-wook

383
00:26:04,041 --> 00:26:07,128
have been campaigning fiercely in Imcheon.

384
00:26:07,211 --> 00:26:10,089
Reporter Kim I-yeong has more
from the heated scene.

385
00:26:10,173 --> 00:26:11,924
To make our Imcheon

386
00:26:12,008 --> 00:26:16,929
the happiest city in all of Korea

387
00:26:17,513 --> 00:26:19,515
I, Kim Seon-jung

388
00:26:19,599 --> 00:26:22,143
together with the citizens of Imcheon

389
00:26:22,435 --> 00:26:25,021
will lead the way.

390
00:26:25,104 --> 00:26:28,357
- Kim Seon-jung!
- Kim Seon-jung!

391
00:26:28,441 --> 00:26:29,901
Please, place your trust in me

392
00:26:29,984 --> 00:26:32,612
candidate number two, Han Gyeong-wook.

393
00:26:32,945 --> 00:26:34,405
If I, Han Gyeong-wook

394
00:26:34,488 --> 00:26:36,657
am elected Mayor of Imcheon

395
00:26:36,782 --> 00:26:39,535
by developing a large-scale
tourism complex

396
00:26:39,619 --> 00:26:41,120
I will make our Yeongseon Island...

397
00:26:41,495 --> 00:26:45,541
into South Korea's premier
tourist destination.

398
00:26:47,126 --> 00:26:52,048
Han Gyeong-wook!
Candidate number two, Han Gyeong-wook!

399
00:26:52,131 --> 00:26:57,970
Candidate number two, Han Gyeong-wook!

400
00:27:01,682 --> 00:27:03,184
I was watching that.
Why did you turn it off?

401
00:27:03,643 --> 00:27:04,769
Because it's loud.

402
00:27:04,852 --> 00:27:07,438
You know how vital this election is
for Yeongseon Island?

403
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,692
Han Gyeong-wook absolutely has to
win this election

404
00:27:11,776 --> 00:27:14,111
but then this Kim Seon-jung guy
popped up out of nowhere.

405
00:27:15,363 --> 00:27:16,989
And why does it have to be
Han Gyeong-wook?

406
00:27:17,073 --> 00:27:19,784
I've been a deliveryman for 20 years.

407
00:27:20,409 --> 00:27:23,162
I can tell just by looking at someone
if they're going to ask for freebies

408
00:27:23,246 --> 00:27:25,289
or try to skip out on the bill.
I just know.

409
00:27:25,373 --> 00:27:26,415
But look at Kim Seon-jung.

410
00:27:26,791 --> 00:27:30,169
Do you think a bookworm teacher
can handle politics?

411
00:27:33,506 --> 00:27:34,757
But this Han Gyeong-wook guy

412
00:27:35,091 --> 00:27:37,760
he has a completely different
aura about him.

413
00:27:38,094 --> 00:27:40,346
He was at the National Intel Service
and a two-term congressman.

414
00:27:40,429 --> 00:27:43,224
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected

415
00:27:43,307 --> 00:27:45,101
and makes Yeongseon Island
a special tourist zone

416
00:27:45,393 --> 00:27:49,563
- this place will skyrocket.
- Stop the chit-chat, huh?

417
00:27:49,647 --> 00:27:50,648
Ho-myeong.

418
00:27:51,274 --> 00:27:52,441
Go make a delivery.

419
00:27:53,067 --> 00:27:54,735
Mr. Kim should go.

420
00:27:54,819 --> 00:27:56,195
I have to prep for the dinner rush.

421
00:27:56,279 --> 00:27:57,321
That place...

422
00:27:57,613 --> 00:28:00,116
- is a place Mr. Kim can't go.
- What do you mean?

423
00:28:02,952 --> 00:28:04,662
- Heaven Capital?
- That's the one.

424
00:28:05,454 --> 00:28:08,332
The one where Mr. Kim gets credit
every time he goes.

425
00:28:08,666 --> 00:28:10,376
You're kidding. He has a tab there?

426
00:28:10,459 --> 00:28:11,919
With 20 years of experience?

427
00:28:13,337 --> 00:28:14,630
Since you're going, Ho-myeong

428
00:28:14,839 --> 00:28:16,882
collect all their overdue payments.

429
00:28:17,258 --> 00:28:19,218
O-ran's checking the books today.

430
00:28:19,302 --> 00:28:20,761
If she sees a hole in our sales

431
00:28:20,845 --> 00:28:22,179
do you think she'll let it slide?

432
00:28:23,973 --> 00:28:25,766
You think Ho-myeong
can collect from those guys?

433
00:28:26,183 --> 00:28:28,352
Not a chance. If he does, I'll eat my hat.

434
00:28:29,103 --> 00:28:30,104
You would've had to

435
00:28:30,313 --> 00:28:32,356
eat your hat 90 times by now.

436
00:28:34,317 --> 00:28:36,402
IMCHEON

437
00:28:36,485 --> 00:28:38,487
The case was closed as a suicide.

438
00:28:38,571 --> 00:28:40,197
Why is the prosecution
trying to reopen it?

439
00:28:40,614 --> 00:28:42,908
Didn't Park promise to handle it

440
00:28:42,992 --> 00:28:44,493
without a problem?

441
00:28:44,577 --> 00:28:46,537
After Prosecutor Park's promotion

442
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:48,164
a new one just arrived, right?

443
00:28:48,247 --> 00:28:51,542
The new prosecutor is making a fuss,
insisting on seeing the crime scene.

444
00:28:51,625 --> 00:28:52,626
A new prosecutor?

445
00:28:53,252 --> 00:28:54,879
You don't think
they're onto something, do you?

446
00:28:56,213 --> 00:28:58,257
She can't catch on
if there's nothing to catch on to.

447
00:28:58,758 --> 00:29:00,009
What is she going to do about it now?

448
00:29:02,762 --> 00:29:04,221
Still, don't let your guard down.

449
00:29:04,889 --> 00:29:06,599
Do you know that prosecutor's nickname?

450
00:29:06,974 --> 00:29:07,975
What is it?

451
00:29:08,434 --> 00:29:09,685
They call her Nongae.

452
00:29:09,769 --> 00:29:10,811
You know Nongae, right?

453
00:29:11,020 --> 00:29:13,064
The courtesan jumped in the river,
taking a Japanese general with her.

454
00:29:13,689 --> 00:29:16,359
Once she sinks her teeth into a case,
she takes everyone down with her.

455
00:29:16,776 --> 00:29:17,985
She's a police academy graduate

456
00:29:18,069 --> 00:29:19,570
and worked violent crime for years.

457
00:29:20,112 --> 00:29:21,864
And she was known
as a total psycho there, too.

458
00:29:22,490 --> 00:29:24,700
Even after becoming a prosecutor,
old habits die hard.

459
00:29:24,992 --> 00:29:27,620
She even went after her own superior
for sexual harassment

460
00:29:27,703 --> 00:29:30,039
And rumor is she was demoted for that to
the Imcheon District Prosecutors' Office.

461
00:29:30,122 --> 00:29:31,791
Actually, it's a fact.

462
00:29:33,084 --> 00:29:34,085
Hello.

463
00:29:34,168 --> 00:29:36,879
I'm Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae from the
Imcheon District Prosecutors' Office.

464
00:29:36,962 --> 00:29:38,923
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Yes, a pleasure.

465
00:29:39,006 --> 00:29:42,343
- Right.
- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to gossip.

466
00:29:42,593 --> 00:29:45,054
Don't be. Why apologize
for stating a fact?

467
00:29:46,514 --> 00:29:47,640
Shall we go up?

468
00:29:50,309 --> 00:29:51,352
Don't you have work to do?

469
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,898
Prosecutor.

470
00:29:55,981 --> 00:29:57,358
Wait, Prosecutor!

471
00:29:57,858 --> 00:30:01,404
- Chairman Do must step down!
- Step down!

472
00:30:01,487 --> 00:30:06,117
- No casino on Yeongseon Island!
- Out!

473
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:09,495
Chairman Do of Heaven Casino,
pull out now!

474
00:30:09,578 --> 00:30:12,164
Pull out!

475
00:30:12,248 --> 00:30:15,459
The gambling that's bleeding
us dry must go!

476
00:30:15,793 --> 00:30:18,129
Go!

477
00:30:18,212 --> 00:30:21,674
What's a casino doing
in pristine Yeongseon Island?

478
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:42,194
Welcome.

479
00:31:17,938 --> 00:31:19,315
HEAVEN CAPITAL

480
00:31:25,654 --> 00:31:27,031
I want a taste of heaven too.

481
00:31:27,114 --> 00:31:29,074
Hey, one more round.

482
00:31:29,366 --> 00:31:30,993
You crazy bastard, I'm all out!

483
00:31:32,995 --> 00:31:34,455
You've got to get to heaven, right?

484
00:31:35,664 --> 00:31:37,124
- You can make it.
- No!

485
00:31:37,708 --> 00:31:39,627
No way. What? This is wrong.

486
00:31:42,671 --> 00:31:45,090
Look how you have to bend it. See?
He bent his card just like this.

487
00:31:45,633 --> 00:31:47,551
- Believe me, he bent it like this.
- Delivery!

488
00:31:48,719 --> 00:31:49,929
Hey, over here.

489
00:31:51,555 --> 00:31:52,723
Here you go.

490
00:31:53,057 --> 00:31:54,099
Oh, yes.

491
00:31:54,433 --> 00:31:55,851
Thank you.

492
00:31:58,521 --> 00:31:59,730
Count these.

493
00:32:04,318 --> 00:32:05,903
Hey, the food's here.
Let's eat and then play.

494
00:32:05,986 --> 00:32:07,112
- Yes, sir.
- Yes.

495
00:32:08,113 --> 00:32:09,615
- Hey, clear this stuff.
- Yes, sir.

496
00:32:14,203 --> 00:32:16,622
- What are you doing?
- Including your order

497
00:32:16,705 --> 00:32:18,916
and your outstanding tab,
that'll be 578,000 won.

498
00:32:19,041 --> 00:32:20,334
You can settle your bill first.

499
00:32:20,876 --> 00:32:23,128
Damn, you just made me lose my appetite.

500
00:32:23,212 --> 00:32:24,880
I don't have any money.
Just put it on my tab.

501
00:32:26,131 --> 00:32:28,551
And what's that over there? Scrap paper?

502
00:32:30,636 --> 00:32:31,637
What the hell...

503
00:32:32,888 --> 00:32:33,889
You little punk.

504
00:32:33,973 --> 00:32:35,391
Do you know what that money is for?

505
00:32:35,474 --> 00:32:37,768
If a single bill goes missing,
all hell will break loose in here.

506
00:32:39,103 --> 00:32:41,522
We'll pay you next time,
so just go. All right?

507
00:32:46,652 --> 00:32:49,029
Damn, this punk just won't listen.

508
00:32:50,030 --> 00:32:52,908
What, do you want a beating so bad
your ears will pop?

509
00:33:03,294 --> 00:33:04,753
Hey, what are you doing?

510
00:33:15,264 --> 00:33:16,682
Damn it.

511
00:33:19,935 --> 00:33:21,895
Jeez. Just a nobody.

512
00:33:22,646 --> 00:33:23,856
Acting all tough.

513
00:33:24,064 --> 00:33:25,983
If you don't pay next time...

514
00:33:28,193 --> 00:33:29,403
I won't be making any more deliveries.

515
00:33:29,486 --> 00:33:32,615
Hey, bring more pickled radish
next time, you asshole.

516
00:33:32,698 --> 00:33:34,617
And bring some free fried dumplings.

517
00:33:35,075 --> 00:33:37,369
- We're regulars.
- Hey, don't talk to him like that.

518
00:33:37,494 --> 00:33:38,495
He looks older up close.

519
00:33:38,579 --> 00:33:41,373
Yeah. You should show
