We found her.

783
00:54:00,341 --> 00:54:01,884
She's been in a villa in Imcheon

784
00:54:01,968 --> 00:54:04,345
ever since that day ten years ago.

785
00:54:08,266 --> 00:54:10,017
Why was she hiding out in South Korea?

786
00:54:10,184 --> 00:54:11,185
I don't know.

787
00:54:11,477 --> 00:54:14,063
Maybe she was looking
for the item, just like us.

788
00:54:17,483 --> 00:54:19,318
So what did you find out?

789
00:54:19,569 --> 00:54:20,570
Nothing.

790
00:54:20,903 --> 00:54:22,029
She was found dead.

791
00:54:22,947 --> 00:54:24,991
- How?
- Officially, it's suicide.

792
00:54:25,074 --> 00:54:26,367
But I suspect murder.

793
00:54:26,993 --> 00:54:29,036
When this video was uploaded to NewTube

794
00:54:29,120 --> 00:54:30,538
I think her location was exposed.

795
00:54:32,582 --> 00:54:34,792
It's unlikely the North
is making a move now.

796
00:54:36,210 --> 00:54:38,129
- It was Han Gyeong-wook, wasn't it?
- No, we don't know yet.

797
00:54:38,212 --> 00:54:40,590
What do you mean, no?
You think Han Gyeong-wook is forgetful?

798
00:54:45,553 --> 00:54:47,221
We can't just sit around and do nothing.

799
00:54:47,638 --> 00:54:49,140
Shouldn't we be making a move now too?

800
00:54:49,223 --> 00:54:50,600
No. It's too soon.

801
00:54:52,268 --> 00:54:54,312
A prosecutor has started sniffing
around this case.

802
00:54:54,770 --> 00:54:57,189
I'm keeping an eye on her,
so just wait a little longer.

803
00:54:57,398 --> 00:54:58,399
- Seong-won.
- Listen.

804
00:54:58,858 --> 00:55:00,735
Don't you know how high up
Han Gyeong-wook is going to get?

805
00:55:00,818 --> 00:55:02,945
If we act rashly and expose our location

806
00:55:03,029 --> 00:55:04,739
then it's really over for us. You get me?

807
00:55:04,864 --> 00:55:06,741
So we should just keep sitting
on our hands?

808
00:55:06,824 --> 00:55:07,825
Doesn't this frustrate you at all?

809
00:55:07,909 --> 00:55:10,328
Then go find the location
of Bulgae and the item.

810
00:55:10,661 --> 00:55:12,204
I've told you over and over.

811
00:55:12,288 --> 00:55:15,499
If they were on Yeongseon Island,
I would've found them by now.

812
00:55:15,583 --> 00:55:16,876
The receiver was broken

813
00:55:16,959 --> 00:55:19,211
and Bulgae must have drowned.

814
00:55:19,295 --> 00:55:20,630
Hey, Ho-myeong.

815
00:55:22,173 --> 00:55:25,968
Let's just do something
before it's too late, okay?

816
00:55:26,052 --> 00:55:27,053
I...

817
00:55:27,929 --> 00:55:29,138
Recently, I...

818
00:55:34,018 --> 00:55:35,519
was diagnosed with male menopause.

819
00:55:37,313 --> 00:55:38,439
So you're saying...

820
00:55:38,856 --> 00:55:40,816
all these flare-ups...

821
00:55:41,484 --> 00:55:44,403
and whining are symptoms of menopause?

822
00:55:44,695 --> 00:55:45,696
I don't know.

823
00:55:46,822 --> 00:55:49,700
Sometimes I feel completely drained,
and other times I just get anxious.

824
00:55:50,159 --> 00:55:52,578
The doctor prescribed
some hormone medication

825
00:55:52,662 --> 00:55:54,288
but it doesn't seem to be helping much.

826
00:55:54,789 --> 00:55:55,790
Look.

827
00:55:56,832 --> 00:55:58,125
We're running out of time.

828
00:55:58,584 --> 00:56:01,087
If I keep going like this, I feel like...

829
00:56:02,088 --> 00:56:04,757
I won't be able to get anything done.

830
00:56:19,438 --> 00:56:21,273
PICK UP JI-WOO FROM KINDERGARTEN

831
00:56:21,857 --> 00:56:23,150
Do you have to go pick him up?

832
00:56:23,943 --> 00:56:24,944
Then go.

833
00:56:26,404 --> 00:56:28,197
Go on. I'll give you a call.

834
00:56:46,424 --> 00:56:49,844
YEONGSEON HAENGBOK KINDERGARTEN

835
00:56:49,927 --> 00:56:51,887
One by one. Let's get on on at a time.

836
00:57:13,909 --> 00:57:14,910
Ji-woo.

837
00:57:15,453 --> 00:57:16,454
Hey, Dad.

838
00:57:19,248 --> 00:57:21,292
Should we send you
to an academy too, Ji-woo?

839
00:57:21,584 --> 00:57:22,710
No.

840
00:57:22,793 --> 00:57:24,336
If I go to an academy

841
00:57:24,670 --> 00:57:27,298
you'd have to sell
a hundred bowls of jajangmyeon.

842
00:57:27,590 --> 00:57:30,134
Hey, don't worry about that.
Dad can sell a hundred bowls.

843
00:57:30,301 --> 00:57:31,719
But that's hard on you.

844
00:57:32,303 --> 00:57:33,304
It's okay.

845
00:57:42,354 --> 00:57:43,355
Dad.

846
00:57:49,487 --> 00:57:50,654
Do you...

847
00:57:51,238 --> 00:57:52,239
want this?

848
00:57:57,536 --> 00:57:59,705
Oh, isn't this your favorite

849
00:57:59,789 --> 00:58:01,123
Masked Racer?

850
00:58:01,457 --> 00:58:03,751
Yeah. When you wear it

851
00:58:03,834 --> 00:58:04,877
you get super strong.

852
00:58:05,252 --> 00:58:06,962
This is to cheer you up.

853
00:58:09,632 --> 00:58:10,633
Let's go.

854
00:58:41,497 --> 00:58:42,873
Wel...

855
00:58:48,504 --> 00:58:49,713
...come.

856
00:58:51,215 --> 00:58:52,800
The usual, right?

857
00:59:03,018 --> 00:59:04,145
- Dad.
- Yeah?

858
00:59:04,270 --> 00:59:05,813
He's here. The "Oldboy."

859
00:59:06,313 --> 00:59:07,398
You mean the fried dumpling guy?

860
00:59:08,232 --> 00:59:09,567
I haven't seen him in a while.

861
00:59:22,496 --> 00:59:23,539
Welcome.

862
00:59:25,583 --> 00:59:26,792
We need to talk.

863
00:59:29,170 --> 00:59:30,171
What is it?

864
00:59:32,298 --> 00:59:33,924
About Ji-woo.

865
00:59:34,884 --> 00:59:35,885
Let's enroll him here.

866
00:59:37,636 --> 00:59:38,721
ANDREW ENGLISH

867
00:59:38,804 --> 00:59:40,014
WHAT MAKES ANDREW ENGLISH CLASSES SPECIAL

868
00:59:41,640 --> 00:59:42,725
Oh, forget it.

869
00:59:43,142 --> 00:59:44,977
We don't have the money
for an academy already.

870
00:59:45,352 --> 00:59:46,604
We can send him when he's older.

871
00:59:46,687 --> 00:59:47,730
Hey, Kwon O-ran.

872
00:59:48,189 --> 00:59:49,607
Can't we do this one thing for him?

873
00:59:49,773 --> 00:59:51,317
All of Ji-woo's friends go here.

874
00:59:51,400 --> 00:59:52,860
Of course I want to.

875
00:59:52,943 --> 00:59:54,820
But can you afford it?

876
00:59:54,904 --> 00:59:56,989
You can't even increase our sales.
Don't be ridiculous.

877
01:00:08,209 --> 01:00:10,669
Thank you for calling
Oran Chinese Restaurant.

878
01:00:12,254 --> 01:00:13,255
Sorry?

879
01:00:16,508 --> 01:00:18,177
I understand. Got it.

880
01:00:19,887 --> 01:00:21,430
- A delivery? To where?
- Heaven Capital.

881
01:00:21,889 --> 01:00:23,724
- Heaven Capital.
- Heaven Capital?

882
01:00:25,100 --> 01:00:26,810
I told you not to take their orders!

883
01:00:26,894 --> 01:00:29,063
Why not?
We need to increase sales, don't we?

884
01:00:29,396 --> 01:00:31,148
I'll just collect all the money
they owe us.

885
01:00:31,232 --> 01:00:34,068
Come on, how will you collect from them?

886
01:00:34,151 --> 01:00:35,527
You go then.

887
01:00:35,611 --> 01:00:37,571
- Yes, you go.
- No way. I'm not going.

888
01:00:37,696 --> 01:00:39,073
Why not? You go.

889
01:00:39,156 --> 01:00:40,991
Why are you asking me?
Just send Ho-myeong.

890
01:00:41,075 --> 01:00:42,201
Come on, you can go.

891
01:00:42,284 --> 01:00:44,203
I said I don't want to.
Why do you keep trying to make me?

892
01:00:44,286 --> 01:00:47,373
- You said you could!
- I said, I'll go!

893
01:00:53,295 --> 01:00:54,630
I'm telling you.

894
01:00:55,297 --> 01:00:57,132
I'll collect everything they owe.

895
01:00:57,925 --> 01:00:58,926
Just watch and see

896
01:00:59,093 --> 01:01:00,719
if I can do it or not.

897
01:01:01,470 --> 01:01:02,471
You just watch.

898
01:01:03,597 --> 01:01:04,640
Those eyes...

899
01:01:05,057 --> 01:01:07,268
Those aren't the eyes of the cook
I've been seeing.

900
01:01:11,230 --> 01:01:13,232
They're the eyes I saw
on that ferry ten years ago.

901
01:01:13,607 --> 01:01:15,359
The eyes of a National
Intelligence Service agent.

902
01:01:39,717 --> 01:01:41,260
Welcome.

903
01:01:41,593 --> 01:01:43,470
- Welcome.
- Oh, that's all right.

904
01:02:09,788 --> 01:02:10,789
Seriously.

905
01:02:15,210 --> 01:02:16,211
Oh?

906
01:02:24,428 --> 01:02:25,804
Where are the house deeds?

907
01:02:26,513 --> 01:02:27,514
The deeds?

908
01:02:28,390 --> 01:02:30,351
- What about them?
- Don't you know what that house is?

909
01:02:30,809 --> 01:02:33,145
Grandpa built that house himself.

910
01:02:33,729 --> 01:02:35,272
So what if he did?

911
01:02:35,481 --> 01:02:37,983
The support beams are rotten
and it could collapse any day now.

912
01:02:38,484 --> 01:02:40,819
Better to put it to good use
before it falls apart.

913
01:02:41,195 --> 01:02:42,279
Don't tell me...

914
01:02:45,032 --> 01:02:47,451
I thought of it as a gift
from Grandpa in heaven...

915
01:02:47,534 --> 01:02:48,869
and cashed it in right away. What?

916
01:02:49,161 --> 01:02:50,162
That's a lie.

917
01:02:50,245 --> 01:02:51,830
- You're lying.
- Oh, come on.

918
01:02:52,289 --> 01:02:53,457
You'll jinx it.

919
01:02:55,042 --> 01:02:57,336
If this pays off,
we'll make a hundred times our money.

920
01:02:57,628 --> 01:02:58,670
When it does

921
01:02:59,088 --> 01:03:01,465
I'll buy you a kick-ass new apartment

922
01:03:01,965 --> 01:03:03,300
so just sit back and watch, okay?

923
01:03:03,384 --> 01:03:05,260
You need to snap out of it.

924
01:03:09,181 --> 01:03:10,808
HEAVEN CAPITAL

925
01:03:11,183 --> 01:03:12,935
You sold it to them, didn't you?

926
01:03:13,102 --> 01:03:14,603
I'm going to get it back.

927
01:03:14,686 --> 01:03:15,979
You wait here.

928
01:03:18,023 --> 01:03:19,775
They'll kill you if you go there.

929
01:03:21,110 --> 01:03:22,236
Unbelievable.

930
01:03:26,657 --> 01:03:27,783
Good luck.

931
01:03:31,161 --> 01:03:32,329
Yes, come on in.

932
01:03:33,122 --> 01:03:34,957
All right, you can go now. Win big.

933
01:03:38,710 --> 01:03:39,753
How can I help you?

934
01:03:40,629 --> 01:03:42,589
My nephew used the house deed

935
01:03:42,673 --> 01:03:45,342
to borrow some money.

936
01:03:45,759 --> 01:03:47,177
I'll pay back the loan

937
01:03:47,261 --> 01:03:49,138
but you cannot sell that house.

938
01:03:49,596 --> 01:03:51,390
- You're here for the deed.
- Yes.

939
01:03:51,723 --> 01:03:53,559
- Have a seat.
- Oh, dear.

940
01:03:56,937 --> 01:03:57,938
What about the interest?

941
01:04:00,023 --> 01:04:01,358
He said he borrowed it just now.

942
01:04:01,442 --> 01:04:03,527
Just now? How long ago?

943
01:04:03,944 --> 01:04:05,237
An hour, maybe two.

944
01:04:05,487 --> 01:04:07,197
One or two hours. In that case

945
01:04:07,531 --> 01:04:10,284
for one hour, that's 3.6 million won

946
01:04:10,367 --> 01:04:13,203
and for two hours, it's 7.2 million.

947
01:04:13,537 --> 01:04:15,539
He just borrowed it.
How can it already be 7.2 million?

948
01:04:15,622 --> 01:04:18,083
Look, if you borrow money,
you have to pay the interest.

949
01:04:18,500 --> 01:04:20,586
What you're doing is completely illegal!

950
01:04:21,086 --> 01:04:24,089
Damn it. Why bring up
"illegal" in here, huh?

951
01:04:24,590 --> 01:04:26,675
Give it to me.
I need to leave with that deed.

952
01:04:29,052 --> 01:04:32,264
Why so many pains in the ass
these days, huh?

953
01:04:32,681 --> 01:04:34,433
Hey, you. Get up. You hear me?

954
01:04:37,186 --> 01:04:38,187
Mister.

955
01:04:39,146 --> 01:04:40,606
If you borrowed money

956
01:04:40,939 --> 01:04:42,274
you pay

957
01:04:42,441 --> 01:04:43,650
the interest. Got it?

958
01:04:43,734 --> 01:04:45,235
I just want the deed.

959
01:04:46,862 --> 01:04:47,905
This little...

960
01:04:49,281 --> 01:04:53,452
- Shut down the casinos!
- Shut them down!

961
01:04:53,535 --> 01:04:57,456
A casino in pristine
Yeongseon Island? It's unacceptable!

962
01:05:12,679 --> 01:05:15,724
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

963
01:05:27,027 --> 01:05:28,862
What... Is he dead?

964
01:05:28,946 --> 01:05:30,989
Hey, get him out.

965
01:05:31,323 --> 01:05:32,658
Hey, mister.

966
01:05:32,950 --> 01:05:33,951
Go sleep it off at home.

967
01:05:35,160 --> 01:05:38,705
Never fall back!
A Republic warrior is never weak!

968
01:05:45,587 --> 01:05:48,549
That's right!
Rise up and destroy our enemies!

969
01:05:48,632 --> 01:05:50,300
The enemies of the Republic...

970
01:05:50,842 --> 01:05:54,429
- will be annihilated!
- Come on, get up.

971
01:05:54,513 --> 01:05:55,681
Come on, get up.

972
01:05:56,098 --> 01:05:57,641
I said go sleep it off at home.

973
01:06:05,816 --> 01:06:07,067
What's wrong with his eyes?

974
01:06:14,866 --> 01:06:15,909
What the hell?

975
01:06:19,788 --> 01:06:21,540
- What the hell?
- Who is this bastard?

976
01:07:45,082 --> 01:07:46,458
I finally found him.

977
01:07:47,918 --> 01:07:48,919
Bulgae.

978
01:07:51,505 --> 01:07:53,507
SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM SANG-KYUNG, KWON
YUL, AHN NAE-SANG, PARK JI-HWAN

979
01:07:53,590 --> 01:07:55,384
KIM JAE-HWA, KO KYU-PHIL, AND HAN
EUN-SEONG FOR THEIR SPECIAL APPEARANCES.

980
01:07:56,009 --> 01:07:58,428
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

981
01:08:10,440 --> 01:08:11,441
He's made his move.

982
01:08:11,525 --> 01:08:13,610
The guy we've been watching for ten years.

983
01:08:13,694 --> 01:08:15,487
She was no ordinary civilian.

984
01:08:15,570 --> 01:08:16,863
A 007 agent.

985
01:08:16,947 --> 01:08:19,199
I made sure she won't go

986
01:08:19,282 --> 01:08:20,909
near the case again.

987
01:08:21,159 --> 01:08:22,911
It's on the house for our regulars.

988
01:08:23,120 --> 01:08:24,121
Are you crazy?

989
01:08:24,204 --> 01:08:25,914
Did I go out and mess around like you did?

990
01:08:26,248 --> 01:08:28,834
You started this whole mess
over an island?

991
01:08:28,917 --> 01:08:30,460
I have a favor to ask.

992
01:08:30,544 --> 01:08:35,173
If we say Seong-won is dead,
the man Jeong Ho-myeong adores

993
01:08:35,674 --> 01:08:38,176
he'll show up at the funeral
no matter what.

994
01:08:38,260 --> 01:08:39,261
Boss!

995
01:08:39,761 --> 01:08:41,596
Now I'm sure of it.
